</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF90FFC9D3D7FEA8FB81FE5F" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Head and pronotum greenish yellow, posterior margin of crown with median and lateral spot on either side of median line, one lateral spot on anterior region of pronotum more widely placed than that on crown, dark brown; posterior and lateral margins of pronotum whitish with brown markings especially on lateral margins. Scutum and scutellum brownish yellow marked with dark brown and scutum with apex and one spot on each lateral margin ivory. Forewing ivory white with dark brown mottling, much rich on apical and subapical cells; median spot pale brown, semicircular, its anterior margin and larger lateral elongate oval spot, dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF90FFC9D387FE70FB0DFD87" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
Head polished, as wide as pronotum. Crown about half as long medially as pronotum, rather 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF90FFC9D66AFE70FA67FE63" box="[1322,1433,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
. Pronotum as long as combined length of scutum and scutellum, transversely wrinkled and polished.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FB46516FF90FFC9D387FD88FEE3FC57" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph id="1711369DFF90FFC9D387FD88FDB3FCA7" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF90FFC9D387FD88FE95FDAB" box="[199,363,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<collectingCountry id="6FB9760DFF90FFC9D387FD88FEFFFDAB" box="[199,257,546,571]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="6FB9760DFF90FFC9D239FD88FE4DFDAB" box="[377,435,546,571]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
pygofer posteriorly conically rounded with macrosetae confined to posterior 
<number id="A16624BAFF90FFC9D655FD89FAB8FDAB" box="[1301,1350,547,571]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.33">0.33</number>
region. Valve 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF90FFC9D39EFDECFEB3FDCF" box="[222,333,582,607]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
, twice as broad at base as long medially, posteriorly narrowed with rounded apex, lateral margins sinuate. Subgenital plate with well developed membranous apical process 
<number id="A16624BAFF90FFC9D09FFDC0FBEEFD13" box="[991,1040,618,643]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.46">0.46</number>
times as long as total length. Style with well developed lateral subapical lobe, apophysis straight, transversely rugose. Connective with stem shorter than arms. Aedeagus with shafts elongate, simple, diverging in ventral view and curved dorsally in lateral view, with small 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF90FFC9D255FD7CFE7CFD7F" box="[277,386,726,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
lobe at midlength along inner margin, gonopore apical on ventral margin; ventral process in lateral view with straight ventral margin, 
<number id="A16624BAFF90FFC9D13CFD51FD61FC83" box="[636,671,763,787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="1.9">1.9</number>
times as long as shaft, triangularly expanded in distal third, then narrowed and thinly produced apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF90FFC9D387FCE8FB50FCEF" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF90FFC9D387FCE8FE78FCCB" box="[199,390,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite approximately twice as broad anteriorly as long medially; posterior margin rather concave laterally, medially produced into lobe with median short V-shaped excavation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1711369DFF90FFC9D387FC26FEE3FC57" blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF90FFC9D387FC26FE97FC33" box="[199,361,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Measurements</emphasis>
: 
<collectingCountry id="6FB9760DFF90FFC9D239FC20FE4CFC33" box="[377,434,906,931]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
<quantity id="D0569B78FF90FFC9D2FAFC21FDBFFC32" box="[442,577,907,931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.7">3.7–3.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="D0569B78FF90FFC9D1C9FC20FCD3FC32" box="[649,813,906,931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="1.275" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.25">1.25–1.30 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 4.0 mm long, 
<quantity id="D0569B78FF90FFC9D7B9FC21FAA0FC32" box="[1273,1374,907,931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.20 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
